{"name": "tiktok-get-info", "metadata": {"name": "tiktok_get_info", "version": "10.10", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "TikTok Info: Module for retrieving and processing information from TikTok.", "upload_time": 1735675167}, "documentation": ["# TikTokInfo\n\n**TikTokInfo** is a Python library and command-line tool for fetching TikTok video metadata, including the author, title, thumbnail, and avatar.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udce6 **Installation**\n```bash\npip install tiktok_info```\n## **run**\n\nrun manually using the command:\n```bash\ntiktok_get -url <url_tiktok> -help```\nrun using the script:\n```bash\nfrom tiktok_get_info import TiktokGetInfo\nurl = \"https://vm.tiktok.com/vid_id/\"\ntiktok = TiktokGetInfo(url)\n\nprint(\"Author:\", tiktok.author())\nprint(\"Title:\", tiktok.title())\nprint(\"Thumbnail:\", tiktok.thumbnail())\nprint(\"Avatar:\", tiktok.avatar())\nprint(\"Endpoint URL:\", tiktok.endpoint())\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info", "documentation": ["TikTok Info: Module for retrieving and processing information from TikTok."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info.cli", "xref": {"fqname": "tiktok_get_info.info.cli", "project": null}}, {"name": "tiktok_get_info.TiktokGetInfo", "xref": {"fqname": "tiktok_get_info.info.TiktokGetInfo", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "tiktok_get_info.info", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info.info.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info.info.TiktokGetInfo", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "tiktok_get_info.info.TiktokGetInfo.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentat